WEBVTT

01:10.028 --> 01:11.064
Can I help you?

01:11.780 --> 01:14.648
I'm lookin', uh, for Ben Aronoff.

01:16.201 --> 01:17.160
I'm afraid he's not in.

01:17.162 --> 01:18.196
Huh.

01:20.664 --> 01:23.657
I've been trying to reach him for a week,
but he hasn't gotten back to me.

01:24.126 --> 01:26.493
I call, and I call, and I call.

01:28.505 --> 01:33.250
Now, look,
my boss is a very wealthy man

01:33.343 --> 01:36.336
who wants to buy a boat.

01:36.430 --> 01:39.173
And he wants to buy the boat
before he goes back to Michigan.

01:39.266 --> 01:41.508
Now, look, I'm just trying
to give this man some money.

01:42.519 --> 01:43.600
I'm Ben.

01:45.480 --> 01:46.812
Why don't you bring your boss in?

01:46.898 --> 01:49.891
We'll show him some boats,
and he can see what he likes.

01:53.488 --> 01:54.488
My boss...

01:56.116 --> 01:57.232
took me from the gutter,

01:58.702 --> 01:59.738
gave me a job.

02:01.330 --> 02:05.290
Everything I have, everything I am,
I owe to him.

02:06.209 --> 02:07.791
I'd do anything for my boss.

02:09.253 --> 02:12.167
Anything... and everything.

02:13.842 --> 02:16.801
I'd never turn my back on my boss.

02:20.349 --> 02:23.183
You tell your boss that I'm done.

02:25.187 --> 02:27.850
I don't owe anybody anything.

02:28.649 --> 02:31.062
I'm paid in full and more so.

02:33.111 --> 02:34.111
You tell him that.

02:36.031 --> 02:38.068
Okay. I'll tell him.

02:39.493 --> 02:40.493
I'll tell him every word.

03:42.764 --> 03:43.764
Hey, Ben.

03:48.061 --> 03:50.141
<i>You couldn't build
a fuckin' outhouse right now</i>

03:50.188 --> 03:52.180
<i>without somebody
blowing up your goddamned car!</i>

03:52.274 --> 03:55.017
Irv, calm the fuck down
and just tell me what happened.

03:55.110 --> 03:57.067
<i>It's over! The war's over. We lost, man.</i>

03:57.154 --> 03:58.861
No. No, what did Lansky say?

03:58.947 --> 04:00.063
<i>You don't get it!</i>

04:00.449 --> 04:01.565
What did he say?

04:01.658 --> 04:03.399
<i>We're done! We're out of business, Ben!</i>

04:03.493 --> 04:06.986
<i>We lost the union!
You still got your cash, right?</i>

04:07.080 --> 04:08.912
Son of a bitch.

04:08.999 --> 04:10.615
<i>- What's that?</i>
- I got it.

04:11.543 --> 04:13.079
<i>You've always been a lucky bastard.</i>

04:13.587 --> 04:15.078
<i>Now, grab your family and your money,</i>

04:15.172 --> 04:17.664
<i>and get the hell out
before things get any worse!</i>

04:20.677 --> 04:25.763
<i>I'm Ben Aronoff, contractor,
entrepreneur, husband, father,</i>

04:25.849 --> 04:27.056
<i>and out of business.</i>

04:27.893 --> 04:29.475
<i>Time to start over.</i>

04:35.233 --> 04:38.726
<i>♪ Let's take off on an adventure ♪</i>

04:38.820 --> 04:41.563
<i>♪ Let's take off fancy-free ♪</i>

04:41.656 --> 04:45.195
<i>♪ Worry not, forget the weather ♪</i>

04:45.285 --> 04:48.574
<i>♪ It's a perfect fantasy ♪</i>

04:48.663 --> 04:51.781
<i>♪ Flying high above the clouds ♪</i>

04:51.875 --> 04:53.992
<i>♪ Without a destination... ♪</i>

04:54.336 --> 04:55.417
You gotta see this.

05:04.888 --> 05:07.631
We are done with winters in New Jersey.

05:08.683 --> 05:09.924
New start, babe.

05:11.228 --> 05:15.222
What about our house, Ben,
and the construction business?

05:16.691 --> 05:17.977
We outgrew it.

05:18.235 --> 05:19.851
Coney Island, New Jersey...

05:22.697 --> 05:25.940
It's a new beginning, Mrs. Aronoff.
We're in Florida.

05:26.034 --> 05:27.070
New life.

05:29.162 --> 05:31.700
I'm not sure what was wrong
with our old life.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.953
You're swinging with Tarzan now. Hang on.

05:43.218 --> 05:45.585
I'm going down to the front desk
to square some things away.

05:55.856 --> 05:57.518
Hey, hey, hey. Come on. Keep it down.

05:57.983 --> 05:59.940
You two over there, Melissa in this bed.

06:01.695 --> 06:02.695
Settle down.

06:03.071 --> 06:05.609
I'm coming back in two minutes,
turning off the lights.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.735
- Hey.
- Bourbon, neat.

06:16.835 --> 06:17.871
You got it.

06:33.476 --> 06:34.683
Two Millers and a highball.

06:34.769 --> 06:35.769
You got it.

06:35.812 --> 06:39.271
Well, if I had known that you were
working, I'd have taken a table.

06:40.317 --> 06:41.558
It's never too late.

06:43.361 --> 06:47.275
- The king of construction, Big Ben.
- Jules!

06:47.365 --> 06:51.450
<i>Now, this guy is Jules Bergman,
Meyer Lansky's main man.</i>

06:51.536 --> 06:53.368
<i>Very connected and very dangerous.</i>

06:53.455 --> 06:56.072
- How are ya?
- Welcome to Miami.

06:56.166 --> 06:58.203
- Thank you.
- Find everything? Family good?

06:58.293 --> 07:00.751
Yes. Yes. We're all settled in upstairs,

07:00.837 --> 07:02.703
and I thank you for the arrangements.

07:02.797 --> 07:04.914
Of course.

07:05.008 --> 07:08.718
They tell me you built
100 houses in one suburb

07:08.803 --> 07:11.136
from dirt to sold in under four months?

07:11.431 --> 07:14.048
More than once. Drove the banks crazy.

07:14.267 --> 07:16.179
Wow. Let's have a seat.

07:17.437 --> 07:18.437
Sure.

07:23.818 --> 07:26.902
So you call me when you're ready
and I'll get you in front of the old man.

07:28.239 --> 07:29.239
Well, how is he?

07:29.658 --> 07:33.618
When Castro came back to Havana
and stole Mr. Lansky's casino,

07:34.287 --> 07:35.403
who took care of me?

07:36.081 --> 07:37.242
Who got me off the island?

07:37.874 --> 07:40.582
If you cut open Mr. Lansky's heart,

07:41.336 --> 07:43.373
he would bleed only loyalty.

07:44.172 --> 07:45.172
To you too, Ben.

07:45.548 --> 07:48.837
You know, I appreciate that.
I appreciate all of it, but I...

07:49.302 --> 07:51.339
I want to do something
on my own here, you know?

07:51.429 --> 07:53.045
A new town, new beginning.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.137
Like the second game of a doubleheader.

07:58.144 --> 08:00.557
So what are your plans?

08:00.897 --> 08:03.640
Like usual, to win.

08:04.818 --> 08:05.818
Okay.

08:07.696 --> 08:08.982
You call me when you're ready.

08:10.281 --> 08:12.364
- Good seeing ya.
- Good to see you.

08:14.035 --> 08:15.035
Thanks.

08:22.460 --> 08:24.122
So, you still want that table?

08:25.547 --> 08:26.583
Why wouldn't I?

08:35.306 --> 08:39.676
<i>♪ Well, its burning vengeance
That fire... ♪</i>

08:39.936 --> 08:43.929
<i>♪ That burning desire
To not do what I'm told ♪</i>

08:44.024 --> 08:46.937
<i>♪ Yeah, to change your perspective ♪</i>

08:47.027 --> 08:48.893
<i>♪ Is long overdue ♪</i>

08:48.987 --> 08:53.277
<i>♪ Return to my roots before I need you ♪</i>

08:53.867 --> 08:58.407
<i>♪ Maybe I said things
that I never meant... ♪</i>

09:00.957 --> 09:01.957
Ben?

09:03.460 --> 09:04.621
Shelley?

09:04.711 --> 09:06.122
Shelley Katz, real-estate law.

09:06.212 --> 09:09.626
<i>Yep, he was a small-time lawyer,
but I needed someone hungry.</i>

09:09.716 --> 09:12.880
- How are ya?
- I'm great. Here's my card.

09:14.304 --> 09:18.264
So do you, uh, make the laws
or do you figure out ways to break 'em?

09:19.309 --> 09:21.141
Scotch rocks.

09:22.187 --> 09:24.725
I make, I break. I just don't do floors.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.014
And what about you, Mr. Big Shot?

09:27.108 --> 09:28.394
No, I checked up on you.

09:28.485 --> 09:30.818
Giant shopping centers,
entire neighborhoods.

09:31.279 --> 09:33.271
What are you planning for Miami? Pyramids?

09:33.615 --> 09:35.072
Just looking for opportunities.

09:35.283 --> 09:39.152
Well, then, for the record,
beyond my hourly rate,

09:39.245 --> 09:41.032
I take 5% of any deal we close.

09:41.122 --> 09:43.660
I'm a lot more than purchase agreements
and deeds of trust.

09:44.334 --> 09:45.334
Three percent.

09:51.091 --> 09:52.091
Okay.

09:55.220 --> 09:56.711
You're too damn easy.

09:56.805 --> 09:58.365
That's my new client discount.

09:58.389 --> 10:01.757
All right, tell me, Counselor,
what do you know about that?

10:01.851 --> 10:03.934
That, my friend...

10:04.896 --> 10:06.558
is what makes Miami Miami.

10:07.315 --> 10:09.102
Beats the hell out of concrete and dirt.

10:09.192 --> 10:10.774
Mm-hmm.

10:14.239 --> 10:17.232
<i>♪ Ah, yeah, ah ♪</i>

10:17.325 --> 10:19.191
<i>♪ So long, so long ♪</i>

10:20.578 --> 10:23.787
<i>♪ I gotta be moving on ♪</i>

10:25.291 --> 10:28.455
<i>♪ Yeah, so long, so long ♪</i>

10:29.712 --> 10:32.750
<i>♪ I gotta be moving on ♪</i>

10:34.300 --> 10:37.293
<i>♪ Yeah, so long, so long ♪</i>

10:38.763 --> 10:40.004
<i>♪ I gotta be... ♪</i>

10:40.098 --> 10:41.098
You're hired.

10:43.393 --> 10:44.393
For what?

10:49.399 --> 10:51.265
- How ya doing?
- Good, you?

10:51.359 --> 10:53.692
- Ben.
- Knocky House, Mr. Aronoff.

10:54.112 --> 10:56.149
Knocky? Is that you real name?

10:56.239 --> 10:58.606
- It's what my friends call me.
- Oh, yeah?

10:58.700 --> 10:59.986
Yeah.

11:00.076 --> 11:01.408
So, what do you got in there?

11:01.494 --> 11:04.362
Twin 327-cubic-inch Chevy V-8s.

11:04.455 --> 11:06.412
Oh, yeah?

11:07.041 --> 11:08.041
Wow.

11:10.503 --> 11:12.870
Yeah! Let's get out there!

11:14.132 --> 11:16.340
- Go ahead, open her up!
- Let's do it!

11:19.971 --> 11:21.007
Use that line!

11:25.435 --> 11:26.596
All right!

11:29.898 --> 11:31.389
Whoo!

11:36.487 --> 11:40.071
<i>And boom, just like that,
I was in love.</i>

11:40.158 --> 11:42.571
<i>The speed, the water, the rush.</i>

11:42.660 --> 11:45.994
<i>I wanted it, I needed it, I would have it.</i>

11:47.624 --> 11:48.624
Ready?

11:50.293 --> 11:52.876
Yeah! I never get tired of this shit!

11:58.551 --> 12:00.087
What do you think, guys?

12:00.553 --> 12:02.715
And you, come here.

12:03.264 --> 12:06.428
How about this? Whose name
do you think should be there?

12:06.517 --> 12:08.304
- Who?
- Yours, silly!

12:13.066 --> 12:14.066
What do you think?

12:15.443 --> 12:19.904
- Yeah, it is kinda sexy.
- Yeah. It is.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.283
<i>Now, this, here, was my first race</i>

12:28.373 --> 12:32.617
<i>against a bunch of rich fat cats
and their toys, and I loved it.</i>

12:45.390 --> 12:47.347
That's the suckers
we gotta beat right there.

12:48.101 --> 12:50.388
Bet they never wrestled
a kid from Brooklyn College.

13:22.593 --> 13:25.051
- Keep the throttle down! Let's go for it!
- I'm on it!

13:36.357 --> 13:37.357
We're doing it!

13:38.067 --> 13:40.024
Yeah!

13:48.911 --> 13:50.447
- Yeah!
- Whoo-hoo!

13:53.458 --> 13:54.665
We're beating 'em!

13:59.505 --> 14:01.918
- We got 'em!
- Ah, yeah!

14:06.888 --> 14:09.631
What was that? Oh!

14:10.058 --> 14:11.738
Hold on,
I'm gonna check the back.

14:12.769 --> 14:13.805
Keep her straight.

14:15.313 --> 14:17.680
Ah, no. God. She's toast.

14:18.775 --> 14:20.812
Okay, forget it. Fine, you know what?

14:21.986 --> 14:23.227
It's fantastic.

14:23.780 --> 14:25.567
Forget the motor, forget everything.

14:25.656 --> 14:27.363
This is fantastic. I love it.

14:34.665 --> 14:37.328
Let's go celebrate,
have a glass of champagne!

14:40.880 --> 14:44.123
<i>♪ There's a thousand miles of highway... ♪</i>

14:45.009 --> 14:51.256
The 233. It's an exclusive boat.
It's an icon for style and speed.

14:51.349 --> 14:54.012
It's the kind of sexy toy
that you can't live without.

14:56.187 --> 14:59.476
Well, you close one door,
and you open another.

14:59.941 --> 15:02.024
A new company with a new vision.

15:02.402 --> 15:07.113
We're building boats that, well,
they push the envelope and break barriers.

15:07.198 --> 15:10.441
Daring, defiant,
and, of course, they're irresistible.

15:10.535 --> 15:13.778
If you want to cross
the finish line first, buy a Donzi.

15:14.372 --> 15:17.831
<i>It's a glorious day here
where a field of 51 racers</i>

15:17.917 --> 15:21.376
<i>stream full speed ahead
from the starting line in Miami.</i>

15:22.171 --> 15:25.630
<i>And there's Dick Bertram
racing his way to his usual position</i>

15:25.716 --> 15:27.252
<i>at the front of the pack.</i>

15:27.927 --> 15:32.092
Mr. Aronoff, tell us about
that first win from Miami to Nassau.

15:32.181 --> 15:33.638
Well, if you really want to win,

15:33.724 --> 15:36.717
sometimes you have to take a chance,
let it all hang out.

15:36.811 --> 15:39.019
As the kids say, it's gotta be your bag.

15:47.363 --> 15:49.901
<i>As the leaders
approach Nassau, it's Bertram,</i>

15:49.991 --> 15:52.654
<i>Webb, and Ben Aronoff.</i>

16:08.885 --> 16:11.878
<i>The racers make the turn
to clear the outside of the island,</i>

16:11.971 --> 16:15.840
<i>and, oh, my!
That's Aronoff placing a big bet,</i>

16:15.933 --> 16:18.300
<i>risking it all on a shortcut
through the shore,</i>

16:18.394 --> 16:20.977
<i>threading the needle
through the jagged rocks!</i>

16:55.890 --> 16:56.890
<i>Aronoff in the 0-0-7.</i>

16:56.933 --> 16:58.014
- Aronoff!
- Yes!

16:58.100 --> 17:00.638
<i>James Bond himself
has taken the lead!</i>

17:09.194 --> 17:11.357
<i>And no one's gonna catch him now!</i>

17:32.009 --> 17:35.548
<i>♪ Lady luck is at my side ♪</i>

17:37.557 --> 17:41.267
<i>♪ This hot streak can't be denied ♪</i>

17:42.270 --> 17:44.762
<i>♪ She has put me at the top ♪</i>

17:44.855 --> 17:47.939
<i>♪ May this run never stop ♪</i>

17:48.025 --> 17:52.315
<i>♪ Bringing wondrous
Riches on this crazy ride ♪</i>

17:53.406 --> 17:56.490
<i>♪ You start the day flat, busted ♪</i>

17:56.576 --> 17:58.784
<i>♪ Deep down in a hole ♪</i>

17:58.869 --> 18:01.953
<i>♪ Now it's seven come eleven
The girls are heaven ♪</i>

18:02.039 --> 18:04.952
<i>♪ And life is on a roll ♪</i>

18:05.042 --> 18:08.535
<i>♪ She's the charm I'm holding fast ♪</i>

18:10.715 --> 18:14.459
<i>♪ He's betting his luck will last ♪</i>

18:15.886 --> 18:20.301
<i>♪ Fortunes come
and go just like the blues ♪</i>

18:20.391 --> 18:25.477
<i>♪ But with lady luck at my side
I'll never lose ♪</i>

18:44.999 --> 18:45.999
Thank you.

18:46.709 --> 18:47.745
No olives.

18:56.093 --> 18:58.176
Hey, Dad! Hey, Dad!

18:58.554 --> 18:59.761
Catch!

19:01.057 --> 19:03.299
Nice spiral, Joe Namath!

19:03.392 --> 19:04.392
Wanna come play with us?

19:05.227 --> 19:07.014
Later. I gotta find your mom.

19:13.986 --> 19:15.727
Oh, wonderful of you to show up.

19:15.821 --> 19:18.985
It got so late last night,
I just stayed at Knocky's.

19:19.533 --> 19:21.570
Yesterday's race,
I think I broke something.

19:22.536 --> 19:23.617
Yes, you did.

19:26.415 --> 19:27.415
Excuse me.

19:46.560 --> 19:49.724
The woman has a tattoo
of Elvis on both thighs,

19:50.022 --> 19:52.765
and she's not convinced
that it looks like Elvis.

19:52.858 --> 19:55.851
So she goes out in the street,
she finds a drunk,

19:56.320 --> 19:58.903
and she lifts up her skirt,
and she says to the drunk,

19:58.989 --> 20:00.321
"Do you recognize these guys?"

20:00.408 --> 20:04.448
And the drunk says,
"I don't know who the twins are,

20:04.537 --> 20:07.029
but the guy in the middle
is definitely Willie Nelson."

20:10.084 --> 20:13.327
I need a drink.
A good joke always makes me thirsty.

20:13.963 --> 20:15.579
Ben, somebody wants to see you.

20:26.183 --> 20:27.264
Mr. Lansky.

20:27.351 --> 20:31.140
<i>Meyer Lansky,
the financial wizard of organized crime.</i>

20:31.230 --> 20:33.222
<i>When he called, you answered.</i>

20:33.733 --> 20:35.975
- Ben Aronoff of Sheepshead Bay.
- How are ya?

20:36.068 --> 20:39.482
- All right. You look good.
- Oh, thanks.

20:39.572 --> 20:42.781
Real good. I've been keeping up with you.

20:42.867 --> 20:44.483
- Oh?
- Yeah.

20:44.577 --> 20:47.365
Our box houses in Jersey
must feel like ages ago

20:47.788 --> 20:50.030
and not nearly as sexy
as those boats of yours.

20:50.958 --> 20:52.790
Build boats, build homes, same thing.

20:52.877 --> 20:55.085
- Not according to my nephew.
- Is that right?

20:55.171 --> 20:56.958
He's gaga for those powerboats of yours.

20:57.047 --> 20:58.047
And those ads.

21:00.176 --> 21:01.176
Hey, Robbie!

21:02.094 --> 21:05.713
<i>That's Robbie Reemer,
Meyer Lansky's little asshole nephew.</i>

21:05.806 --> 21:07.593
Tell us why you like Ben Aronoff.

21:07.683 --> 21:09.675
Because Ben Aronoff has everything!

21:11.896 --> 21:12.932
See?

21:16.901 --> 21:18.437
Still remember Jacob, your father.

21:19.570 --> 21:21.937
He'd be proud of you
selling to that hoity-toity crowd.

21:22.364 --> 21:23.980
Making a stir, making a buck.

21:26.327 --> 21:27.327
But on your own?

21:29.789 --> 21:30.905
New beginnings?

21:32.124 --> 21:33.124
That's crap.

21:34.502 --> 21:36.038
Not wanting to be a bother?

21:37.171 --> 21:38.207
More crap.

21:38.798 --> 21:39.879
We're your family, Benny.

21:41.425 --> 21:42.506
These are your people.

21:45.596 --> 21:48.589
Sometimes you just want
to do some things on your own.

21:53.187 --> 21:56.430
You do that when it
comes to banging shiksas

21:56.524 --> 21:57.731
and betting the ponies.

21:58.400 --> 22:00.187
You don't put
that bullshit in front of me.

22:04.198 --> 22:07.236
You ever seen a head all swelled up?
That's you.

22:08.577 --> 22:10.239
Not good for a goddamn thing.

22:11.038 --> 22:13.530
Don't remember who you are
or where you came from.

22:32.518 --> 22:33.725
Hey. Are you kidding me?

22:33.811 --> 22:35.393
You know him? You know Meyer Lansky?

22:35.479 --> 22:37.892
Oh, fuck Lansky!
I've worked too hard, Shelley,

22:37.982 --> 22:39.769
for him to come in the middle of our shit.

22:39.859 --> 22:41.600
We've got too many big things coming in.

23:57.603 --> 23:59.289
<i>Aronoff's revolutionary Cigarette</i>

23:59.313 --> 24:01.851
<i>has taken offshore powerboat racing
by storm.</i>

24:01.941 --> 24:04.024
<i>At each stop on the European circuit,</i>

24:04.109 --> 24:06.101
<i>the Cigarette has burned through
the record books,</i>

24:06.195 --> 24:08.733
<i>shattering every mark for time and speed.</i>

24:09.573 --> 24:12.316
<i>Up to a fantastic 66 miles an hour,</i>

24:12.409 --> 24:15.402
<i>13 miles an hour faster than
the record set three years ago.</i>

24:15.496 --> 24:20.457
Boats are sex symbols, and, certainly,
the Cigarette boat is a sexy boat,

24:20.542 --> 24:22.204
but we don't market it that way.

24:36.684 --> 24:39.347
It's a man's boat,
and it's a dangerous machine.

24:40.145 --> 24:42.728
<i>And there's Ben Aronoff
speeding home,</i>

24:42.815 --> 24:45.432
<i>heading towards
his seventh victory this season.</i>

24:45.526 --> 24:48.894
<i>One more and he reclaims
the world championship.</i>

25:06.630 --> 25:07.746
Mmm.

25:15.389 --> 25:19.508
My husband would like
to purchase two Cigarette boats.

25:20.060 --> 25:22.017
- Hmm.
- Hmm.

25:22.438 --> 25:25.431
Well, for you,
I'll have to charge him double.

25:30.446 --> 25:34.315
You know, I would have to come
to America, pick them up.

25:34.908 --> 25:35.908
Could you?

25:40.748 --> 25:43.491
Does it ever get cold in, uh, Florida?

25:43.959 --> 25:45.871
Very.

25:46.378 --> 25:49.121
But I could always use some warmth

25:50.090 --> 25:53.128
of the... Tuscan... sun.

25:55.846 --> 25:57.633
Hey, Ben.

25:59.099 --> 26:00.135
Shelley?

26:01.268 --> 26:02.537
I've been lookin' all over for ya.

26:02.561 --> 26:05.224
- Who is this man?
- He's my lawyer.

26:05.314 --> 26:06.600
We gotta talk.

26:09.068 --> 26:11.902
I'll be back. Don't you go.

26:16.825 --> 26:20.444
Now I didn't volunteer,
okay, to run your office,

26:20.537 --> 26:23.575
your business and your family,
for Christ's sake.

26:24.500 --> 26:26.116
I'm just a lawyer, remember?

26:26.585 --> 26:29.077
You flew 3,000 miles to complain?

26:29.171 --> 26:30.787
What are you doing here, Ben?

26:32.091 --> 26:33.673
What are you running away from? Lansky?

26:33.759 --> 26:35.591
I'm busting my ass for our company.

26:35.677 --> 26:38.294
Oh, oh, okay. Yeah, right. I can see that.

26:38.388 --> 26:40.596
Winning races sells boats, Shelley.

26:40.682 --> 26:42.827
Do you throw in the sex with every sale
or do they pay for that, too?

26:42.851 --> 26:46.094
- You better watch your fuckin' mouth.
- Oh, good. Great. Rip me to shreds, Ben,

26:46.188 --> 26:50.148
because then there will be
absolutely nobody running your company.

26:52.528 --> 26:53.735
I'm sorry.

26:55.030 --> 26:56.030
Yeah.

26:58.784 --> 27:01.902
I'm gonna win the world championship
at the end of this month, Shelley.

27:02.663 --> 27:04.871
That's big. It's very big.

27:07.042 --> 27:08.203
<i>Mazel tov.</i>

27:11.213 --> 27:13.296
By the way,
your son just got into college.

27:13.715 --> 27:14.876
He's leaving in a week.

27:16.593 --> 27:18.050
I just thought you'd like to know.

27:19.388 --> 27:21.050
I'll see you back in Florida.

27:40.325 --> 27:42.442
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, yeah ♪</i>

27:43.787 --> 27:46.325
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, yeah ♪</i>

27:47.416 --> 27:50.875
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, yeah ♪</i>

27:53.255 --> 27:55.542
<i>♪ I may have fallen upset ♪</i>

27:56.592 --> 27:59.255
<i>♪ But I won't stop this time ♪</i>

28:00.429 --> 28:03.046
<i>♪ I may have fallen upset ♪</i>

28:04.099 --> 28:06.386
<i>♪ And I'll be gone for a while ♪</i>

28:07.728 --> 28:10.015
<i>♪ You see those cracks in the sidewalk ♪</i>

28:11.398 --> 28:13.685
<i>♪ They're like the cracks in my mind ♪</i>

28:15.110 --> 28:17.022
<i>♪ Don't wanna talk to nobody ♪</i>

28:18.780 --> 28:21.147
<i>♪ I've reached the end of the line ♪</i>

28:24.119 --> 28:26.736
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, yeah ♪</i>

28:27.873 --> 28:29.660
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, yeah ♪</i>

28:31.877 --> 28:33.994
<i>But while I was
winning championships,</i>

28:34.838 --> 28:37.046
<i>I was losing something far more important.</i>

28:53.649 --> 28:54.935
Kathy.

28:57.194 --> 28:58.194
Andrew.

28:59.821 --> 29:02.905
He damaged his spine...
in the car accident.

29:02.991 --> 29:04.152
He's in surgery now.

29:06.370 --> 29:08.077
They say he may not make it.

29:11.792 --> 29:14.079
Don't worry. We'll get this right.

29:14.503 --> 29:16.460
We will get this right.

29:48.620 --> 29:51.704
Andy, you gotta fight through this.

29:54.209 --> 29:55.871
You need to stick around.

29:57.879 --> 30:01.372
You're an Aronoff.
We fight back. We battle.

30:04.136 --> 30:05.502
Okay, this is the deal.

30:05.887 --> 30:08.254
You're gonna get through this,
you're gonna get better,

30:08.765 --> 30:10.631
and you're gonna walk the hell outta here.

30:12.436 --> 30:13.436
You hear me?

30:17.816 --> 30:19.933
I'm gonna be here
all night with you, okay?

30:20.652 --> 30:23.440
I'll be right here.
I'm gonna sleep right there on the couch.

30:24.197 --> 30:27.110
I'm not going anywhere. Okay? Dad's back.

30:32.247 --> 30:33.328
Dad's back.

30:37.252 --> 30:38.333
Baby boy.

31:07.282 --> 31:12.323
Your son had to almost lose his life
to get his father's attention.

31:16.083 --> 31:17.870
What do the rest of us have to do?

31:23.090 --> 31:24.090
Come on.

31:24.925 --> 31:25.925
Come on.

31:50.242 --> 31:52.404
- You got a lot of friends, Ben.
- Do I?

32:02.003 --> 32:03.369
How is he? How's Andrew?

32:06.758 --> 32:08.750
They told me he'll never walk again.

32:14.182 --> 32:15.548
Oh, God.

32:18.854 --> 32:20.174
I mean, he's here, though, right?

32:21.523 --> 32:23.264
He's a tough kid. He'll battle back.

32:24.985 --> 32:27.147
Kathy and I are through. Done.

32:29.489 --> 32:31.196
A long time ago, Ben.

32:33.743 --> 32:36.326
So, how are we doing?

32:40.292 --> 32:41.703
What do you mean? Business-wise?

32:41.793 --> 32:43.079
- Yes.
- Oh.

32:43.920 --> 32:45.440
No, I'm not talking about that right now.

32:45.464 --> 32:46.921
Oh, yes, you are, Shelley.

32:47.007 --> 32:48.373
Actually, no, I'm not.

32:48.467 --> 32:51.835
Just tell me, how are we doing?
What are the numbers? Just tell me.

32:54.556 --> 32:57.596
Look, it's not like every time you win
a race, they gave you a million bucks,

32:58.268 --> 33:01.727
which is half of what it costs to run the
racing team across Europe for the summer.

33:04.816 --> 33:08.605
To be honest,
we can't sell enough hulls a year

33:08.695 --> 33:10.840
to keep the company afloat,
not the way we're running it.

33:10.864 --> 33:12.480
We're in a deep hole, Ben.

33:20.499 --> 33:21.499
Well...

33:22.834 --> 33:23.834
I'll fix it.

33:24.878 --> 33:26.164
Like I always do.

33:47.484 --> 33:51.899
<i>I knew where I had to go,
and he was waiting for me.</i>

33:53.532 --> 33:55.023
<i>I thought I got out,</i>

33:56.117 --> 33:57.608
<i>but you never get out.</i>

34:34.739 --> 34:35.946
Great to see you, Ben.

34:48.378 --> 34:50.745
<i>Someone else
was waiting for me, too.</i>

35:03.643 --> 35:05.225
Hell of a day out there, champ.

35:06.771 --> 35:08.854
But they're still
running the horses at noon.

35:09.357 --> 35:13.977
So, what do you say we burn a grand or two

35:14.529 --> 35:16.441
and remember what real beer tastes like?

35:20.201 --> 35:21.442
Andy.

35:22.662 --> 35:26.747
I'm telling ya, feeling sorry
for yourself ain't gonna work.

35:27.125 --> 35:30.163
You gotta get out there, boy.
You gotta live again.

35:32.714 --> 35:36.048
Come on, buddy. Let's go out.
Let's go out to the track.

35:39.721 --> 35:40.721
Okay, that's it.

35:45.810 --> 35:47.051
I fuckin' hate you!

36:03.578 --> 36:04.578
Well, I love you.

36:22.597 --> 36:23.597
What do I see?

36:24.349 --> 36:25.349
I see a smile?

36:26.559 --> 36:28.050
You know you're still fucking crazy?

36:28.853 --> 36:30.560
Yeah. I know that.

36:31.731 --> 36:33.097
Now let's go to the track.

36:35.068 --> 36:37.776
<i>And they're off!</i>

36:37.862 --> 36:39.023
Here we go!

36:39.698 --> 36:43.282
Here we go! Come on! Come on!

36:43.785 --> 36:48.325
Do it! Five! Come on! Five! Come on!

36:48.415 --> 36:52.455
- You got this!
- Do it! Do it! Do it!

36:52.544 --> 36:53.955
Five! Come on!

36:54.504 --> 36:57.963
Yes! There it is! Look, look!
Look, look, look! We got it!

36:58.049 --> 36:59.256
Yes! Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

36:59.342 --> 37:01.629
Bring it home! Whoo!

37:01.720 --> 37:03.677
- That's it, baby!
- We got it!

37:06.266 --> 37:08.349
Come on, five!

37:15.525 --> 37:16.891
Whoo-hoo!

37:17.736 --> 37:19.773
Two wins today, buddy. Not bad.

37:21.030 --> 37:22.030
You like it?

37:23.199 --> 37:25.236
Yeah, what's not to like? It was fun.

37:25.326 --> 37:29.445
You know, I got a line
on a big stable up north in Ocala.

37:29.539 --> 37:31.246
What do you say we buy it?

37:31.332 --> 37:33.449
We fill it with thoroughbreds,

37:33.543 --> 37:35.205
and you run the whole damn thing.

37:36.671 --> 37:38.271
I don't know anything about horses, Dad.

37:39.299 --> 37:42.588
I didn't know anything
about boats or building houses.

37:45.096 --> 37:47.634
See this? See that?

37:48.933 --> 37:52.267
That was my whole year's salary
when I was a gym teacher in Brooklyn.

37:53.188 --> 37:54.850
How do you think I did that?

37:54.939 --> 37:56.396
How do you think I made that happen?

37:57.025 --> 38:00.143
I busted my ass
and I beat the fuckin' odds.

38:01.780 --> 38:02.861
So can you.

38:05.658 --> 38:08.321
- You really think so?
- Ah! I know so.

38:10.038 --> 38:11.870
<i>I was never really there for him,</i>

38:12.373 --> 38:17.243
<i>but I wanted to buy him some happiness,
and he took that money... and ran.</i>

38:23.676 --> 38:24.676
<i>Coño.</i>

38:31.810 --> 38:33.051
Top-of-the-line model.

38:37.774 --> 38:39.982
- How much?
- Retail, 32K.

38:41.820 --> 38:44.403
- You'll take 35?
- 45.

38:52.872 --> 38:56.206
Fuck it. We take together, pair.

38:56.292 --> 38:59.285
- Say, 80K.
- 100K.

39:11.224 --> 39:12.224
Okay.

39:13.101 --> 39:14.308
Ah.

39:14.394 --> 39:15.475
Deal.

39:16.312 --> 39:17.632
What do you want the title to be?

39:17.689 --> 39:21.228
Pick a name. A good one.

39:21.901 --> 39:23.938
Nobody wants to explain
where the cash came from.

39:24.779 --> 39:27.567
- Come with me.
- I like this guy.

39:40.295 --> 39:42.787
<i>And just like their drug-sniffing dogs,</i>

39:42.881 --> 39:44.838
<i>once the DEA got the scent,</i>

39:44.924 --> 39:46.290
<i>they were hard to shake.</i>

39:47.468 --> 39:49.004
Mr. Aronoff!

39:49.345 --> 39:50.927
Stuart Lopez, DEA.

39:53.391 --> 39:54.391
Nice boat!

39:54.809 --> 39:56.345
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

39:57.478 --> 39:58.594
Office.

39:59.314 --> 40:00.475
I'll see you there.

40:04.611 --> 40:07.649
Look, no surprise to you, Mr. Aronoff.

40:07.739 --> 40:10.356
Cigarette boats are a big hit
on the drug-running circuit.

40:10.783 --> 40:13.150
Lately, we busted a lot of
smugglers driving your boats.

40:13.244 --> 40:14.244
My boats?

40:14.246 --> 40:16.407
I mean, boats manufactured
by your company.

40:16.497 --> 40:18.329
Ah, yes.

40:18.458 --> 40:21.951
The problem is the sales names are fiction
and the hull numbers don't make any sense.

40:22.754 --> 40:23.754
We sell boats.

40:23.796 --> 40:27.164
They're registered, re-registered,
sold and resold.

40:27.258 --> 40:30.547
And, by the way, the resale value
is through the fucking roof.

40:32.055 --> 40:34.798
Do you record the hull numbers
associated with each purchase?

40:34.891 --> 40:38.225
Now you know, and I know,
that it's illegal

40:38.311 --> 40:40.098
not to record those numbers, so...

40:40.772 --> 40:41.979
where are you going with this?

40:42.815 --> 40:44.351
Just doing our job, Mr. Aronoff.

40:44.776 --> 40:47.314
You know, catching bad guys.

40:47.403 --> 40:52.865
Okay, so do you go to Smith and Wesson
every time you haul someone in with a gun?

40:53.618 --> 40:55.575
Look, I make boats. Fast boats.

40:55.662 --> 40:59.827
People want them.
They come in here, I take their ID,

40:59.916 --> 41:03.409
they pay me money, and boom,
they are standing

41:03.503 --> 41:06.871
in the cockpit of a speedboat,
a very sexy speedboat.

41:07.507 --> 41:08.507
So what do you want me to do?

41:08.509 --> 41:10.625
To chase them down and fingerprint them?

41:10.718 --> 41:14.632
We'd put you on our payroll if you did.

41:15.765 --> 41:16.765
That's good.

41:34.575 --> 41:36.237
- Whoa, watch out.
- Out of the road!

41:44.752 --> 41:46.414
Make sure you get the name right.

41:46.754 --> 41:48.416
I'm Robbie fuckin' Reemer!

41:53.052 --> 41:54.839
<i>With the Feds closing in on him,</i>

41:55.471 --> 41:57.508
<i>Meyer Lansky fled to Israel,</i>

41:58.141 --> 42:00.929
<i>but Israel's welcome
to all Jews from anywhere</i>

42:01.019 --> 42:04.854
<i>did not include him,
and he was forced back to Miami.</i>

42:10.778 --> 42:12.940
Hey, Ben. Come.

42:21.622 --> 42:24.956
Meyer, welcome back. How are ya?

42:25.043 --> 42:26.329
Ben.

42:30.214 --> 42:32.706
They tell me that you made
all the payments back to me.

42:33.426 --> 42:36.089
Yes. Almost six months ago.

42:36.554 --> 42:37.965
We've just been rolling them out.

42:38.056 --> 42:41.675
You know, it's a...
Business booming and it's...

42:41.768 --> 42:44.932
Just... everyone and their brother
wants a speedboat.

42:45.897 --> 42:47.263
Here, let me get that.

42:51.611 --> 42:53.898
Yeah, it's good.

42:58.993 --> 43:00.780
You self-satisfied little prick.

43:06.709 --> 43:07.825
You took the money, Ben.

43:12.299 --> 43:13.834
You took the fuckin' money!

43:14.217 --> 43:16.630
You didn't borrow it
from Household Finance!

43:18.805 --> 43:20.965
You don't think that I got other things
to worry about?

43:21.265 --> 43:23.882
Besides Ben Aronoff
and his little fuckin' boat business?

43:23.976 --> 43:25.308
Meyer. Meyer, please.

43:25.937 --> 43:27.303
You know I'm grateful,

43:27.396 --> 43:30.139
and you also know
I went to great lengths to...

43:30.233 --> 43:31.314
Stop!

43:36.322 --> 43:38.530
We are growing our operations on the seas.

43:40.159 --> 43:42.492
You're clean and that helps.

43:42.995 --> 43:44.076
Don't play dumb.

43:45.164 --> 43:46.764
You know exactly what I'm talking about.

43:46.833 --> 43:48.995
Now, there is a big difference

43:49.085 --> 43:52.169
between what we had agreed upon
and what you're implying here.

43:52.672 --> 43:54.834
You'll do your fuckin' part!

44:04.475 --> 44:05.932
- Hey, champ.
- Hey.

44:07.520 --> 44:08.727
I got a fucking name!

44:11.232 --> 44:12.313
You remember me, right?

44:14.026 --> 44:16.439
Because Ben Aronoff has everything.

44:17.738 --> 44:18.738
Meyer's nephew.

44:19.866 --> 44:20.866
Meyer's nephew?

44:21.576 --> 44:22.576
You're not?

44:24.203 --> 44:26.286
I'm racing now! You better watch out!

44:26.372 --> 44:27.783
Oh, yeah? We'll be lookin' for ya.

44:58.029 --> 44:59.270
Good to see ya.

45:01.908 --> 45:02.944
I gotta see it.

45:13.044 --> 45:14.160
We're good?

45:15.421 --> 45:17.788
Yeah, we're good. It's this way.

45:25.681 --> 45:27.138
1.5 tons.

45:27.225 --> 45:28.932
Now, that's what I'm talking about.

45:29.018 --> 45:31.852
- Boys, get to work.
- Yes, sir.

45:39.987 --> 45:41.444
Whoo!

45:41.906 --> 45:45.274
It tastes stronger every day, man.

45:45.618 --> 45:48.201
Hey, boss! You want some?

45:48.287 --> 45:49.653
Yeah, pass it over here!

45:51.249 --> 45:52.865
Some fuckin' good weed!

45:52.959 --> 45:54.978
<i>See if you see him.
He's coming at you. Late-model C.</i>

45:55.002 --> 45:56.962
Yeah, we got eyes on him right now.

45:57.296 --> 46:01.165
Here he comes. Here he comes.
Everybody set?

46:01.259 --> 46:02.986
- Yes, sir. All set.
- All set. All set.

46:03.010 --> 46:04.717
Go! Go! Go!

46:06.764 --> 46:08.505
- Fuck!
- Oh, shit! Fuck!

46:09.308 --> 46:10.668
<i>This is the Coast Guard!</i>

46:10.726 --> 46:13.810
<i>Stop your boat! Stop your boat!</i>

46:31.497 --> 46:32.497
Oh, man!

46:33.499 --> 46:34.660
You okay? You okay?

46:35.042 --> 46:36.999
Shit! Brad looks bad!

46:37.086 --> 46:38.086
Grab the wheel!

46:41.716 --> 46:43.082
You're gonna be okay!

46:47.555 --> 46:48.591
Move!

46:51.851 --> 46:54.264
<i>Pick him up! Pick him up!</i>

47:10.202 --> 47:11.613
Need some repairs, champ.

47:12.246 --> 47:15.660
I got some holes in her,
and I want you to take care of it.

47:21.297 --> 47:22.297
Mmm.

47:23.257 --> 47:25.715
No. We don't do those kind of repairs.

47:26.010 --> 47:27.046
I'm sure you do.

47:27.887 --> 47:30.254
As a matter of fact, I know you do.

47:31.349 --> 47:33.869
And, while you're at it, how about you
put some of them custom seat-stitchings

47:33.893 --> 47:35.253
you've been doing on the new ones?

47:35.811 --> 47:37.143
I'd really like that.

47:37.897 --> 47:40.981
And, when you're done,
you can run the bill over to my uncle.

47:41.650 --> 47:42.857
Let me ask you something.

47:43.402 --> 47:45.359
- Hmm?
- Did your uncle teach you how to swim?

48:02.004 --> 48:03.745
Let's get a drink. Come on.

48:04.215 --> 48:05.609
This is so fun being with you, Ben.

48:05.633 --> 48:08.467
- Manhattan, two cherries?
- Let's do champagne.

48:08.552 --> 48:09.552
Champagne!

48:11.889 --> 48:13.300
Are they getting younger, champ,

48:13.391 --> 48:15.098
or are you just getting
more distinguished?

48:15.476 --> 48:17.934
Do you really want to start this
with your best-paying client?

48:18.020 --> 48:19.352
I'm not starting anything.

48:20.356 --> 48:23.315
- Uh, you are the famous boat racer?
- Yes.

48:23.401 --> 48:25.233
Yes.

48:25.319 --> 48:27.561
So shall I call you "The Animal?"

48:27.655 --> 48:28.771
Yes.

48:32.868 --> 48:34.234
You can call me "The Animal."

48:43.838 --> 48:45.955
- Your Majesty.
- King Hussein of Jordan?

48:46.465 --> 48:48.206
Now, you know this is the spot!

48:57.435 --> 49:00.849
<i>And, oh, my God, she walked in.</i>

49:17.288 --> 49:18.404
I've known him for years.

49:19.915 --> 49:20.951
I'll be right back.

49:27.131 --> 49:29.623
How's my favorite king?

49:30.926 --> 49:33.418
You didn't realize?
I stopped speaking to you

49:33.512 --> 49:35.970
after you sold those Donzis
to the Israelis,

49:36.056 --> 49:37.968
and they turned them into torpedo boats.

49:38.225 --> 49:40.808
Anything to beat the damn Arabs.

49:40.895 --> 49:42.136
Still the same Ben.

49:42.813 --> 49:43.894
My friends.

49:44.648 --> 49:47.857
You can't say "Miami"
without saying Ben Aronoff.

49:48.235 --> 49:51.319
And this lovely creature is Emily Gowen.

49:52.114 --> 49:53.114
My pleasure.

49:53.157 --> 49:56.946
I lure her from New York
to come slum with us on the beach.

49:57.495 --> 50:00.283
I wouldn't call it that, Your Highness.

50:02.708 --> 50:05.200
- Emily, how are you?
- Oh, you made it.

50:06.295 --> 50:07.536
So...

51:48.939 --> 51:51.727
Last night at The Jockey Club,
this motherfucker came up to me

51:51.817 --> 51:53.900
and said, "Get down
to your warehouse right now."

51:53.986 --> 51:56.353
So I dump my date, I speed down,

51:57.031 --> 51:59.444
I open up the fucking gates, and bam!

51:59.533 --> 52:02.025
There are two boats pulling up,
filled with marijuana.

52:02.119 --> 52:05.988
They take that shit through my warehouse,
put 'em on trucks,

52:06.540 --> 52:07.576
and this is what we get.

52:07.666 --> 52:09.248
This is how you go to jail, man.

52:11.086 --> 52:13.294
Ben, uh, what are we doin' here?

52:13.380 --> 52:15.588
This is Lansky saying, "Do your bit!"

52:16.091 --> 52:19.084
And, on top of that,
he wants me to fly down to the Caymans

52:19.178 --> 52:20.840
and make deposits on their money.

52:22.848 --> 52:24.214
That's not my biggest problem.

52:25.059 --> 52:26.641
You know anything about Emily Gowen?

52:26.727 --> 52:28.593
- You gotta be kidding me, right?
- No.

52:28.687 --> 52:30.790
Besides the fact
that she's King Hussein's girlfriend?

52:30.814 --> 52:33.022
Shelley, he's got two fuckin' wives.

52:33.108 --> 52:37.694
And bodyguards,
and an enormous bankroll, and an army.

52:38.113 --> 52:40.480
Please. Just get me the number, will ya?

52:53.170 --> 52:55.207
Hey! Hey, Emily!

52:56.465 --> 52:58.545
There's a guy up there,
says he wants to talk to you.

53:14.858 --> 53:16.065
I didn't know what to bring,

53:16.151 --> 53:19.144
but I saw that you drank this
the other night at the club.

53:19.571 --> 53:21.563
You're nothing if not persistent,
Ben Aronoff.

53:24.118 --> 53:25.154
I got your calls.

53:25.953 --> 53:28.161
Examine a man's faults,
you'll find his virtues.

53:36.296 --> 53:39.334
I have some stuff to do.
You're welcome to come along.

53:40.134 --> 53:41.170
Thank you.

53:42.261 --> 53:44.969
So, have you been riding
since you were a kid?

53:45.889 --> 53:47.676
- That's all I lived for.
- Hmm.

53:47.808 --> 53:49.970
Until my mother threw me into modeling.

53:52.354 --> 53:53.561
Have you ever been on a horse?

53:56.024 --> 53:58.311
I have a tough enough time
staying on a boat.

53:58.402 --> 54:01.270
No horses, but I do like horse races.

54:01.947 --> 54:03.563
- Yeah, me too.
- Yeah.

54:04.908 --> 54:08.697
There's nothing like it when they're
really running and turning for home.

54:08.787 --> 54:10.949
It is the best 20 seconds on Earth.

54:11.039 --> 54:15.625
Yeah. The sound of those hooves
and the muscle and grit.

54:15.711 --> 54:18.795
It's amazing. It's truth.

54:19.423 --> 54:20.423
Yeah.

54:21.300 --> 54:24.418
Marlboro, he's my favorite,
so I always make time to feed him.

54:24.511 --> 54:28.972
If he had his way, he'd bust right
outta here and just keep running, right?

54:29.057 --> 54:31.265
I know how you feel, Marlboro.

54:31.351 --> 54:33.308
May I feed him? May I?

54:33.645 --> 54:35.056
Here, let me try.

54:37.608 --> 54:39.065
There you go. Oops.

54:39.526 --> 54:41.286
Let me try again. Here you go.

54:41.361 --> 54:44.479
Here. There you go. Wow.

54:48.285 --> 54:50.072
You're pretty comfortable around a horse.

54:51.163 --> 54:52.745
You sure you haven't been on one?

54:54.458 --> 54:57.872
- You're a natural.
- I wouldn't say that.

55:08.180 --> 55:09.546
It's gonna get worse.

55:10.766 --> 55:12.928
Hey, there's no shame
in sitting this one out.

55:13.018 --> 55:14.600
Half the field's already dropped.

55:14.895 --> 55:15.895
Really?

55:16.730 --> 55:19.814
You know, I knew a guy once,
looked a lot like you.

55:20.359 --> 55:22.817
He said,
"I'll never get tired of this shit!"

55:23.529 --> 55:24.690
- Come on.
- Yeah.

55:55.018 --> 55:56.018
Oh.

55:59.314 --> 56:03.058
I'm no sailor,
but those dark clouds can't be good.

56:04.862 --> 56:07.149
Do they have rain-outs
like they do in baseball?

56:08.574 --> 56:09.906
Let me explain, sweetheart.

56:09.992 --> 56:13.030
In the glorious sport
of offshore powerboat racing,

56:13.453 --> 56:15.740
you take the beating of a lifetime
for hours,

56:16.206 --> 56:19.370
there's no one there to cheer you on,
and if you get hurt,

56:19.459 --> 56:22.998
which Ben does every single race,
you can't quit.

56:23.088 --> 56:25.205
You gotta just keep going
until you see land.

56:26.383 --> 56:27.749
That's good to know, Mr. Katz,

56:27.843 --> 56:30.301
that the chances of Ben standing me up
on this date are...

56:30.637 --> 56:35.007
Zero to none. Okay?
And would ya please call me Shelley?

56:35.767 --> 56:38.384
Okay. Shelley.

56:51.450 --> 56:53.612
<i>I've got Ben Aronoff up front.</i>

56:53.702 --> 56:56.285
<i>Brassfield coming up in second.</i>

56:57.873 --> 56:59.330
<i>And there's Robbie Reemer</i>

56:59.416 --> 57:01.499
<i>fighting the waves and keeping it close.</i>

57:05.255 --> 57:08.373
<i>And there's Brassfield! He's making a run!</i>

57:08.884 --> 57:10.876
<i>Oh, he crashed! Brassfield crashed!</i>

57:12.721 --> 57:15.885
Circle back! Circle back!
We're gonna need a rescue!

57:37.371 --> 57:38.657
This is suicide!

57:40.248 --> 57:42.911
Come on.

57:43.293 --> 57:46.411
Come on! Oh, come on! Get over there!

57:52.844 --> 57:54.927
We're turning the fuck around!

58:01.103 --> 58:03.345
- We're the last one left!
- Keep going!

58:08.235 --> 58:13.731
- We can still turn!
- No! Full throttle! Full throttle!

58:14.866 --> 58:16.653
We can make it!

58:29.423 --> 58:30.459
Yeah?

58:34.302 --> 58:35.509
Yeah, okay.

58:36.805 --> 58:38.216
Well, keep me posted.

58:49.901 --> 58:52.484
All boats accounted for, except for Ben's.

58:55.782 --> 58:57.114
It's been over six hours.

58:58.285 --> 59:00.045
If he was gonna make it,
he'd be here by now.

59:04.082 --> 59:05.082
I hardly know him...

59:05.876 --> 59:08.334
Or... knew him.

59:12.716 --> 59:16.380
But he gets to you, your Ben.

59:49.252 --> 59:51.995
He made it! He made it!

59:54.257 --> 59:56.465
He made it! He made it!

01:00:50.230 --> 01:00:51.562
Hey, Robbie!

01:00:51.648 --> 01:00:55.141
I just heard Ben Aronoff
made it to Nassau, won the race.

01:00:56.027 --> 01:00:57.484
Thought you'd want to know.

