01:04:51.554 --> 01:04:52.554
It's okay.

01:04:54.099 --> 01:04:55.016
Morning.

01:04:55.018 --> 01:04:57.383
Morning. Bobo. Bo.

01:05:00.105 --> 01:05:01.186
I'll be home early.

01:05:07.529 --> 01:05:11.443
<i>Our goal is to break
the power of the mob in America</i>

01:05:11.533 --> 01:05:12.990
<i>and nothing short of it.</i>

01:05:13.076 --> 01:05:15.989
<i>We mean to end their profits,
imprison their members</i>

01:05:16.079 --> 01:05:18.412
<i>and cripple their organizations.</i>

01:05:21.835 --> 01:05:24.373
<i>If anyone doubts what federal,
state and local authorities</i>

01:05:24.462 --> 01:05:26.670
<i>working with the support
of the people can achieve,</i>

01:05:26.756 --> 01:05:30.215
<i>let them come to South Florida,
and see, here, what we've seen today.</i>

01:05:31.428 --> 01:05:32.839
Ugh!

01:06:11.176 --> 01:06:13.213
<i>Meyer Lansky
is the reputed crime boss</i>

01:06:13.303 --> 01:06:15.090
<i>who was once said to have boasted,</i>

01:06:15.180 --> 01:06:19.094
<i>"We are bigger than U.S. steel,"
but today, dead at the age of 81,</i>

01:06:19.184 --> 01:06:22.928
<i>Lansky was buried in a Miami cemetery
in a plain coffin.</i>

01:06:27.233 --> 01:06:28.419
I don't like it, Shelley.

01:06:28.443 --> 01:06:30.810
I still have mud on my shoes
from Lansky's funeral.

01:06:30.904 --> 01:06:34.193
That's 36 hours ago. Why?
Why this meeting?

01:06:34.282 --> 01:06:35.551
Hey, it's just a courtesy, all right?

01:06:35.575 --> 01:06:37.615
We're gonna sit down with them.
We're in, we're out.

01:06:38.620 --> 01:06:40.862
- Hey. Hey, Al.
- Shelley!

01:06:41.706 --> 01:06:43.413
- Ben.
- Hey.

01:06:45.376 --> 01:06:46.376
Okay.

01:06:53.134 --> 01:06:54.545
I want to keep this short.

01:06:55.136 --> 01:06:59.597
Our company, Comanche, is building
a new plant on Thunderboat Alley.

01:07:00.683 --> 01:07:03.642
Really? Have you bought the land yet?

01:07:03.728 --> 01:07:05.264
That's why we're all here.

01:07:05.813 --> 01:07:08.430
Well, good. So why don't you
just put a proposal together,

01:07:08.525 --> 01:07:12.439
present it to Shelley, and I'll review it?

01:07:12.529 --> 01:07:13.645
Simple.

01:07:13.738 --> 01:07:15.229
Good. Let's go.

01:07:15.323 --> 01:07:16.323
Sit down, Ben.

01:07:18.743 --> 01:07:21.076
This is bullshit, and you know it.

01:07:22.247 --> 01:07:24.580
Hey, hey, no, Ben. Ben, Ben.

01:07:24.666 --> 01:07:26.032
- What?
- Let's come to peace.

01:07:26.125 --> 01:07:28.788
For you. That's it. What? What is it?

01:07:31.631 --> 01:07:35.591
Here's the proposal.
Only it's not really a proposal.

01:07:36.344 --> 01:07:38.301
You're gonna give us the land.

01:07:40.682 --> 01:07:42.218
AI's gonna take care of the deed,

01:07:42.308 --> 01:07:44.470
you and your lawyer pal here
are gonna sign it.

01:07:45.270 --> 01:07:48.479
And then we're gonna build our
own boat factory right down the street.

01:07:48.731 --> 01:07:51.018
We'll be neighbors.
Now, won't that be great?

01:07:51.693 --> 01:07:54.777
You're fucking crazy.
Come on! Jesus Christ!

01:07:54.862 --> 01:07:57.070
We'll even throw
a big fuckin' block party, Ben!

01:07:57.156 --> 01:07:58.317
- Good!
- You're invited!

01:07:59.200 --> 01:08:00.611
Motherfuckers!

01:08:01.077 --> 01:08:03.597
It's just dirt, Ben. What do you care?
You're not using it anyway.

01:08:03.621 --> 01:08:05.015
You know how much money they're making.

01:08:05.039 --> 01:08:06.325
Why do they have to rip me off?

01:08:06.416 --> 01:08:08.123
You're making a lot of money too, buddy.

01:08:08.751 --> 01:08:10.431
And you're rich enough to not give a damn.

01:08:11.421 --> 01:08:14.414
Besides, that kid is sloppy. All right?
He's all over the place.

01:08:14.507 --> 01:08:17.250
He'll be back in prison
before you know it, while you, my friend,

01:08:17.343 --> 01:08:19.756
have a new company to run.
U.S.A. Racing, baby.

01:08:20.095 --> 01:08:21.095
I'll call you tomorrow.

01:08:30.523 --> 01:08:31.542
Safe flight, buddy.

01:08:31.566 --> 01:08:33.979
I can't believe this, Shelley. Last run.

01:08:34.068 --> 01:08:36.151
I'm with you. Last run for me, too!

01:08:38.323 --> 01:08:39.564
Last time, Shelley!

01:09:10.270 --> 01:09:11.728
Ha-ha! Big Ben!

01:09:11.814 --> 01:09:13.145
Mister Vice President.

01:09:13.232 --> 01:09:15.064
Oh, go tell it to the Marines.

01:09:15.151 --> 01:09:16.629
I'm happy with just plain old George.

01:09:16.653 --> 01:09:17.653
I'm happy with Ben.

01:09:19.363 --> 01:09:20.444
- How are ya?
- How are you?

01:09:20.490 --> 01:09:22.447
This is Nick Brady.
He's a long-time friend.

01:09:22.533 --> 01:09:25.071
He runs a big bank in New York...
Dillon Read.

01:09:25.161 --> 01:09:26.197
Oh, well.

01:09:26.287 --> 01:09:29.140
I've been hearing loads about you, too,
'cause George is always bragging.

01:09:29.165 --> 01:09:31.747
- Is that right?
- You need someone to manage your millions.

01:09:31.834 --> 01:09:33.062
Nick runs a pretty good outfit.

01:09:33.086 --> 01:09:34.372
- I'll keep that in mind.
- Yeah.

01:09:34.462 --> 01:09:35.919
- Is that it?
- That's it.

01:09:36.546 --> 01:09:38.709
- Come.
- Holy smokes.

01:09:38.800 --> 01:09:40.152
Hey, what do you think of the jacket?

01:09:40.176 --> 01:09:43.340
Uh, you look like a... like a boat racer.

01:09:43.429 --> 01:09:45.591
- Barbara thinks I look silly.
- How is Barbara?

01:09:45.682 --> 01:09:47.002
Oh, she's doing great. Thank you.

01:09:47.308 --> 01:09:49.220
Well, it certainly passes the eye test.

01:09:49.769 --> 01:09:50.805
Mm-hmm.

01:09:50.895 --> 01:09:52.413
What are you gonna call this one?

01:09:52.438 --> 01:09:53.645
Blue Thunder.

01:09:53.731 --> 01:09:55.209
- Blue Thunder.
- Blue Thunder.

01:09:55.233 --> 01:09:57.153
- Let's take her for a ride.
- Yeah, let's do it.

