when you get home late at night.

01:16:00.014 --> 01:16:01.755
It makes me feel unwanted.

01:16:01.849 --> 01:16:04.341
I didn't want to wake you. I love you.

01:16:15.529 --> 01:16:16.770
You know the Blue Thunder deal?

01:16:17.323 --> 01:16:20.031
All that hoopla about catching
bad guys with better boats?

01:16:20.618 --> 01:16:21.950
I just got off with customs,

01:16:22.870 --> 01:16:24.389
and they've been asked
to make checks payable

01:16:24.413 --> 01:16:27.451
to a new company, Super Chief South.

01:16:28.667 --> 01:16:29.953
Robbie Reemer owns that company.

01:16:32.129 --> 01:16:34.232
So you're telling me the biggest
dope smuggler in the country

01:16:34.256 --> 01:16:36.496
is in charge of building the boats
intended to catch him?

01:16:38.886 --> 01:16:41.424
I thought the Blue Thunder contract
went out to Ben Aronoff.

01:16:42.014 --> 01:16:43.095
Yeah, it did.

01:16:43.724 --> 01:16:46.137
An old friend.

01:17:10.251 --> 01:17:12.334
Please. Sit.

01:17:28.644 --> 01:17:30.010
No reason to coat this, Ben,

01:17:30.729 --> 01:17:33.597
but our Dade County guys
tell us the Feds are digging around,

01:17:33.941 --> 01:17:35.148
looking into everything.

01:17:35.234 --> 01:17:37.851
Dope-running, money, the whole operation.

01:17:37.945 --> 01:17:40.423
A Grand Jury's collecting evidence
faster than we can clock it.

01:17:40.447 --> 01:17:43.281
It's bad.
And it's moving right up our asses.

01:17:45.244 --> 01:17:49.238
So you're all personally suspects?

01:17:50.082 --> 01:17:51.914
Some fuckin' banker in Europe

01:17:52.001 --> 01:17:54.835
is ratting us all the fuck out
for a fuckin' plea deal.

01:17:56.380 --> 01:17:57.621
So what do you want me to do?

01:18:00.926 --> 01:18:04.966
How about some basic co-operation?

01:18:05.347 --> 01:18:07.304
- Really?
- Really.

01:18:08.976 --> 01:18:11.079
You know what?
You better bring your fuckin' goons here

01:18:11.103 --> 01:18:13.186
'cause I'll cut your fuckin' heart out.

01:18:13.522 --> 01:18:16.686
Get this asshole outta here,
or this meeting ends!

01:18:16.775 --> 01:18:20.689
I'm not kidding! Get him out! Get out!

01:18:20.779 --> 01:18:23.772
Fuckin' handle this. Handle this!

01:18:33.959 --> 01:18:36.167
Look, Ben...

01:18:38.130 --> 01:18:40.417
we need to put some assets
back under your name,

01:18:40.507 --> 01:18:42.590
back under the purview of your companies.

01:18:43.177 --> 01:18:46.841
Remove it from the Feds' reach...
for a period.

01:18:49.683 --> 01:18:53.927
You guys are precious.
You really, really are precious.

01:18:54.021 --> 01:18:55.307
This is serious, Ben.

01:18:55.397 --> 01:18:56.397
Hmm.

01:19:00.110 --> 01:19:02.397
Fuck it. Move the assets.

01:19:03.113 --> 01:19:06.151
But you put every single one
of them in my name,

01:19:06.242 --> 01:19:07.608
not my company's name.

01:19:08.160 --> 01:19:10.618
And then good luck on getting them back.

01:19:10.704 --> 01:19:12.070
Nobody's winning here, Ben.

01:19:12.706 --> 01:19:14.663
We're just talking about surviving.

01:19:15.542 --> 01:19:17.033
This is bigger than you,

01:19:17.544 --> 01:19:19.957
or Robbie, or fuckin' anyone.

01:19:21.048 --> 01:19:24.086
Well, guess what? It ain't my problem.

01:19:42.987 --> 01:19:44.353
What have you got us into?

01:19:47.741 --> 01:19:48.741
He has a gun.

01:19:50.869 --> 01:19:53.486
- Where's Willie?
- He's in his room.

01:19:54.498 --> 01:19:55.739
You go to him.

01:19:56.709 --> 01:19:58.200
You go to him.

01:20:06.969 --> 01:20:09.131
Nice place. Nice family.

01:20:10.639 --> 01:20:12.221
I hate to see you lose it all.

01:20:14.852 --> 01:20:16.093
Now it's my family?

01:20:17.104 --> 01:20:18.811
You're gonna get subpoenaed,

01:20:20.065 --> 01:20:22.273
and all kinds of people
are worried about it.

01:20:23.110 --> 01:20:25.102
Worried about what you're gonna say.

01:20:27.406 --> 01:20:28.772
But I tell them...

01:20:29.700 --> 01:20:32.443
I'm sure old Ben's gonna play ball.

01:20:32.536 --> 01:20:33.652
He's on the team.

01:20:34.371 --> 01:20:36.863
That is what teammates do, right?

01:20:37.458 --> 01:20:38.619
Get out.

01:20:38.917 --> 01:20:41.204
- Get the fuck outta here.
- Good luck.

01:20:46.342 --> 01:20:49.050
- You've been warned, Ben.
- Get the fuck out.

01:20:53.432 --> 01:20:55.719
Tell me something. You owe me something.

01:20:56.393 --> 01:20:58.510
I have to get you out of here.

01:20:58.604 --> 01:21:01.392
I want you to get on the phone
and call your sister in New York

01:21:01.482 --> 01:21:03.442
and tell her that you're on the way.
Just do that.

01:21:03.525 --> 01:21:04.525
What is going on?

01:21:04.568 --> 01:21:07.652
I will tell you everything
when you get to New York. I promise.

01:21:08.322 --> 01:21:10.109
I am scared.

01:21:10.199 --> 01:21:13.943
I am scared for you.
I am scared for all of us.

01:21:14.036 --> 01:21:16.028
Don't be. Don't be.

01:21:18.707 --> 01:21:22.997
- I love you.
- God. I love you, too.

01:21:24.088 --> 01:21:25.204
Okay.

01:21:37.559 --> 01:21:40.302
Now, listen. Listen. Listen to me.

01:21:40.396 --> 01:21:41.728
We're gonna be fine.

01:21:41.814 --> 01:21:45.478
I'll call your sister with the number
you can reach me. Okay?

01:21:45.567 --> 01:21:47.229
I'll call you when I get in.

01:21:47.694 --> 01:21:49.856
Okay. Okay. Go, go. Go.

01:22:04.711 --> 01:22:07.169
Slow down. Slow down. Take it easy.

01:22:20.394 --> 01:22:21.635
Don't alarm her.

01:22:22.271 --> 01:22:24.388
Plenty of time
before we get to the causeway.

01:23:14.740 --> 01:23:16.026
Stay with her.

01:23:16.992 --> 01:23:19.359
Go, go, go, go. Don't let her go too far.

01:24:12.548 --> 01:24:14.005
- Emily.
<i>- Hey.</i>

01:24:14.091 --> 01:24:16.708
Oh, thank God. Hey, babe.

01:24:16.802 --> 01:24:18.964
<i>You're safe? No problems?</i>

01:24:19.054 --> 01:24:24.971
Yeah. Yeah, William's already in bed,
and Aunt Cynthia's been incredible.

01:24:26.770 --> 01:24:28.932
Except, I think I forgot
what winter was like.

01:24:29.022 --> 01:24:32.060
Yeah, man.
Oh, I used to hate Jersey winters.

01:24:33.527 --> 01:24:36.270
Well, it's pretty here. You should come.

01:24:36.363 --> 01:24:37.363
<i>I can't, babe.</i>

01:24:38.323 --> 01:24:39.939
You know, I can't put you guys at risk.

01:24:42.536 --> 01:24:44.277
So are you gonna tell me?

01:24:47.040 --> 01:24:48.156
Okay, look.

01:24:48.750 --> 01:24:52.539
Over the years, I did business
with a lot of shady guys, okay?

01:24:53.088 --> 01:24:54.499
And I stepped on some toes.

01:24:56.550 --> 01:24:58.166
I don't know what that means.

01:24:58.635 --> 01:25:02.504
It means that I made promises
to people that I can no longer keep.

01:25:02.598 --> 01:25:04.510
<i>And it's come back to haunt me.</i>

01:25:06.476 --> 01:25:07.557
The guy in the living room?

01:25:07.644 --> 01:25:11.763
The guy in the living room is just
one of a whole line of people

01:25:11.857 --> 01:25:14.565
going all the way back
to my days in New Jersey.

01:25:15.068 --> 01:25:17.776
- The mob?
- Oh, fuck...

01:25:19.031 --> 01:25:20.522
Okay, babe, listen.

01:25:23.535 --> 01:25:25.822
There is a big court case.

01:25:26.413 --> 01:25:28.154
A lot of people are gonna go down.

01:25:28.248 --> 01:25:32.458
<i>And the Feds are pushing hard
on everyone, including me.</i>

01:25:33.378 --> 01:25:34.378
So...

01:25:34.713 --> 01:25:39.083
So, you and me, our lives,
it's just all been one big lie?

01:25:39.926 --> 01:25:41.212
Babe, don't say that.

01:25:41.762 --> 01:25:45.096
When I fuckin' saw you,
I dropped to my knees.

01:25:45.182 --> 01:25:46.514
You fuckin' stoned me.

01:25:47.768 --> 01:25:49.725
<i>You're the one who cleared up my life.</i>

01:25:52.648 --> 01:25:53.684
Then run.

01:25:53.774 --> 01:25:55.481
I can't do that now, babe.

01:25:55.942 --> 01:25:57.183
<i>I'm a fighter too, Ben.</i>

01:25:57.277 --> 01:26:00.145
If you're in a fight,
I wanna be right at your side.

01:26:03.283 --> 01:26:04.490
Just hang in there.

01:26:05.243 --> 01:26:06.700
<i>Hang in there for me, baby.</i>

01:26:09.039 --> 01:26:10.120
I love you.

01:26:30.936 --> 01:26:31.936
Yeah?

01:26:33.772 --> 01:26:34.888
Hey.

01:26:36.066 --> 01:26:37.102
Uh-huh.

01:26:38.318 --> 01:26:39.479
Uh-huh.

01:26:40.362 --> 01:26:41.443
Where?

01:26:44.282 --> 01:26:45.614
What's the name?

01:26:58.463 --> 01:27:01.080
Okay, Dutch.
It's a straight shot down to 75.

01:27:01.466 --> 01:27:04.174
It's a little bend in Orlando,
but we don't change highways, so...

01:27:04.553 --> 01:27:06.761
- Okay.
- Yeah. Take it easy.

01:27:08.432 --> 01:27:14.178
- Hey. Come on.
- What? No tickets.

01:27:14.271 --> 01:27:17.605
- No tickets.
- No tickets.

01:27:17.983 --> 01:27:21.476
- No tickets!
- Yeah, no tickets.

01:27:23.196 --> 01:27:26.189
- That means the cops are...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. I remember.

01:28:02.944 --> 01:28:07.063
- Morning.
- Morning. Agent...?

01:28:07.157 --> 01:28:08.739
- Lopez.
- Ah!

01:28:09.659 --> 01:28:11.616
- It's been a while, hasn't it?
- Yes.

01:28:13.205 --> 01:28:15.788
A couple of goombahs wound up
in the E.R. last night.

01:28:15.916 --> 01:28:19.535
Smashed into by a Ford Bronco.
Thought you might know something about it.

01:28:24.007 --> 01:28:26.499
I... ran your plates.

01:28:26.593 --> 01:28:29.711
Put the word out, called around,
and bingo.

01:28:30.388 --> 01:28:32.630
It's kinda weird to find
a Mercedes in this parking lot.

01:28:33.058 --> 01:28:36.472
Although, more likely to find
Robbie Reemer with a couple of hookers.

01:28:37.020 --> 01:28:40.889
- What do you want?
- I'm just curious.

01:28:41.441 --> 01:28:45.185
You know, I really am,
'cause your name keeps popping up

01:28:45.278 --> 01:28:47.270
all over this big-ass investigation.

01:28:48.657 --> 01:28:52.025
You know, a guy who was friends
with kings and queens,

01:28:52.118 --> 01:28:54.110
and a goddamn Vice-President,

01:28:54.204 --> 01:28:58.414
sells his multi-million-dollar government
contract to a mobbed up hustler?

01:28:59.125 --> 01:29:02.459
- It's just business.
- Just business?

01:29:04.798 --> 01:29:07.541
Look, you know, I read this book
once by a Jewish guy.

01:29:08.176 --> 01:29:12.796
He said, "People who have a why to live
can bear almost anything."

01:29:13.473 --> 01:29:14.473
What's your why, Ben?

01:29:15.725 --> 01:29:17.136
Let me tell you something.

01:29:17.727 --> 01:29:21.311
Sometimes it doesn't matter
who you are or what you have.

01:29:22.065 --> 01:29:23.977
It's just too hard to say no.

01:29:26.069 --> 01:29:28.732
Do you have a plan?
'Cause you're in with a rough crowd.

01:29:29.155 --> 01:29:32.774
You can help us, and we can help you.

01:29:33.285 --> 01:29:36.073
Water's calmed down,
we just gotta stay in the boat.

01:29:37.372 --> 01:29:38.372
Hang on.

01:29:39.249 --> 01:29:40.410
That's a risky bet.

01:29:41.167 --> 01:29:42.999
I've been winning with it my whole life.

01:29:43.461 --> 01:29:47.455
Now, if you're not going to arrest me,
you have a nice day.

01:30:02.147 --> 01:30:04.355
Hey, buddy, there he is.

01:30:04.774 --> 01:30:07.482
Secret rendezvous on the beach.

01:30:08.862 --> 01:30:09.898
Black.

01:30:12.824 --> 01:30:14.941
I spoke to my buddy at the D.A.'s office.

01:30:15.035 --> 01:30:16.242
They won't confirm anything.

01:30:17.621 --> 01:30:19.640
On the other hand, they would
have told me to take a hike

01:30:19.664 --> 01:30:20.864
if the subpoena wasn't coming.

01:30:23.043 --> 01:30:24.284
If it's typed, it's ripe.

01:30:24.836 --> 01:30:26.476
You're getting served, buddy-o, tomorrow.

01:30:28.673 --> 01:30:32.587
- That's actually great news.
- Really? How's that?

01:30:33.011 --> 01:30:35.219
Once you get served,
they'll keep you safe.

01:30:35.305 --> 01:30:38.844
The Reemers, whoever, they're not
gonna touch you once that happens.

01:30:39.434 --> 01:30:41.972
They'll bring the Feds
and the Miami-Dade P.D.

01:30:42.562 --> 01:30:44.053
Dirty as they are, no one wants that.

01:30:45.023 --> 01:30:48.061
25 years
of your giving me high-end advice,

01:30:48.151 --> 01:30:52.942
and it all boils down to "Stick around
till you get served."

01:30:53.031 --> 01:30:54.112
That's the ticket.

01:30:54.199 --> 01:30:57.192
Here's something.
Now, you're involved in this, too.

01:31:03.083 --> 01:31:06.042
All right, I'll tell you what.
Head back to your office,

01:31:06.461 --> 01:31:08.168
grab your cash, anything you want,

01:31:08.588 --> 01:31:11.581
meet me at the Hollywood Marina,
we'll take my boat and just...

01:31:12.217 --> 01:31:15.460
just disappear for the day.
All right? We'll wait it out.

01:31:15.553 --> 01:31:20.469
Just two good ol' boys gone fishing.
Sounds good.

01:31:38.827 --> 01:31:42.696
Millie, it's me.
Anyone there I should know about?

01:31:42.789 --> 01:31:44.872
<i>Nothing moving but the waves, Ben.</i>

01:31:44.958 --> 01:31:45.994
Good.

01:32:51.566 --> 01:32:52.727
Can I help you?

01:32:53.234 --> 01:32:56.102
I'm lookin', uh, for Ben Aronoff.

01:32:57.572 --> 01:32:58.653
I'm afraid he's not in.

01:32:58.907 --> 01:33:00.148
Huh.

01:33:01.993 --> 01:33:05.111
I've been trying to reach him for a week,
but he hasn't gotten back to me.

01:33:05.705 --> 01:33:07.992
I call, and I call, and I call.

01:33:10.210 --> 01:33:14.875
Now, look, my boss
is a very wealthy man

01:33:14.964 --> 01:33:17.923
who wants to buy a boat.

01:33:18.009 --> 01:33:21.127
And he wants to buy the boat
before he goes back to Michigan.

01:33:21.221 --> 01:33:23.429
Now, look, I'm just trying to give
this man some money.

01:33:23.890 --> 01:33:24.926
I'm Ben.

01:33:26.726 --> 01:33:29.639
Why don't you bring your boss in,
we'll show him some boats,

01:33:29.729 --> 01:33:31.470
and he can see what he likes?

01:33:31.564 --> 01:33:32.564
My boss...

01:33:34.484 --> 01:33:35.645
took me from the gutter,

01:33:36.820 --> 01:33:37.936
gave me a job.

01:33:39.489 --> 01:33:43.984
Everything I have, everything I am,
I owe to him.

01:33:44.536 --> 01:33:46.152
I'd do anything for my boss.

01:33:47.455 --> 01:33:50.448
Anything... and everything.

01:33:52.001 --> 01:33:54.789
I'd never turn my back on my boss.

01:33:58.383 --> 01:34:01.126
You tell your boss that I'm done.

01:34:03.138 --> 01:34:05.551
I don't owe anybody anything.

01:34:06.516 --> 01:34:09.054
I'm paid in full and more so.

01:34:10.895 --> 01:34:12.932
- You tell him that.
- I'll tell him.

01:34:14.107 --> 01:34:15.473
I'll tell him every word.

01:35:22.634 --> 01:35:23.634
Hey, Ben.

01:36:31.703 --> 01:36:35.447
<i>I'm Ben Aronoff.
I was on top of the world.</i>

01:36:36.165 --> 01:36:39.624
<i>I loved, I created, I won.</i>

01:36:40.712 --> 01:36:42.328
<i>It was one hell of a race.</i>

01:36:43.256 --> 01:36:46.340
<i>Internationally known
race-boat designer, Don Aronow,</i>

01:36:46.426 --> 01:36:48.509
<i>was shot to death
this afternoon outside...</i>

01:36:48.594 --> 01:36:51.632
<i>...two-time world offshore
powerboat racing champion...</i>

01:36:51.723 --> 01:36:53.760
<i>...pronounced dead
at about 5:00...</i>

01:36:53.850 --> 01:36:55.160
<i>...the Godfather, that is him.</i>

01:36:55.184 --> 01:36:58.177
<i>You could call him the Henry Ford
of powerboats. He is the man...</i>

01:36:58.271 --> 01:37:01.890
<i>...starting up and developing
the sport of offshore powerboat racing...</i>

01:37:01.983 --> 01:37:03.127
<i>...raced his creations</i>

01:37:03.151 --> 01:37:05.393
<i>to three national
and two world championships.</i>

01:37:05.486 --> 01:37:09.070
<i>His friends are badly shaken,
unable to understand why anyone would...</i>
